[[File:An Unix Fabric Shaver.jpg|thumb|Unix Fabric Shaver]] The '''fabric shaver''' (also known as a '''lint shaver''' or '''fuzz remover''') is a handheld electrical device that has a rotating blade underneath a blade net. It allows users to remove [[Lint (material)|fuzz]] on a fabric without damaging the fabric.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wisegeek.com/what-is-a-fabric-shaver.htm|title=What is a Fabric Shaver? (with pictures)|publisher=}}</ref> It can be applied on different fabric-made items such as [[Bedding|bedding]], [[Curtain|curtain]] or [[Carpet|carpet]], but mostly used for removing fuzz on a clothes, especially [[Sweater|sweaters]], [[Hoodie|hoodies]], or clothes made by [[Wool|wool]], [[Angora_wool|angora]] or [[Cashmere_wool|cashmere]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/strategist/2017/02/the-fabric-shaver-i-trust-on-my-favorite-sweaters.html|title=The Sweater De-Piller That I Trust on My Most Beloved Cashmere|first=Katy|last=Schneider|publisher=}}</ref> The fabric shaver can be powered by two different ways; using a [[Battery_charger|battery charger]] or a [[Dry_cell|dry cell]]. To use the fabric shaver, all the user has to do is check its battery and then press on/off button.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://terms.naver.com/entry.nhn?docId=2464090&cid=51399&categoryId=51399|title=보풀제거기|publisher=}}</ref> [[File:Part of Unix fabric shaver blade net.jpg|thumb|Part of Unix fabric shaver: blade net]] [[File:Part of Unix fabric shaver blades.jpg|thumb|Part of Unix fabric shaver: blades]]
