== India ==
A [[garrison]] engineer holds the rank of executive engineer in the [[Military Engineer Services|Indian Defense Service of Engineers]]. Garrisson Engineer is a designation which is  held either by a civilian officer of M.E.S. or by a military officer of the rank of Lt Col. The Garrison engineer's staff includes at least three assistant garrison engineers, a barrack stores officer, an accounts officer, and junior engineers. Responsibilities of the position include procuring contracts and executing them. One of the elected members of the [[cantonment board]] has to be a former garrison engineer.

The first [[Indian people|Indian]] to become an officiating garrison engineer was [[Rai Bahadur]] Pandit Ram Prasad Tewari, who served in the [[Military Engineer Service]]s from 1880 to 1920.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vibhutewary.com/data/ebooks/tewari/tewari.pdf#page=9|title=Testimonial and Services of Rai Bahadur Pandit Ram Prasad Tewari, G. E., M. E. S., Darbari (1880-1920)}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vibhutewary.com/data/ebooks/tewari/tewari.pdf#page=18|title=Testimonial and Services of Rai Bahadur Pandit Ram Prasad Tewari, G. E., M. E. S., Darbari (1880-1920)}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vibhutewary.com/data/ebooks/tewari/tewari%20original.pdf#page=2|title=Copy of Testimonial and Services of Rai Bahadur Pandit Ram Prasad Tewari, G. E., M. E. S., Darbari (1880-1920)}}</ref>

